IJM Declines Most in Week After UOB-Kay Hian Downgrades Stock

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-10-04T08:44:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/ijm-declines-most-in-week-after-uob-kay-hian-downgrades-stock.html
IJM Corp., a Malaysian builder, fell
the most in a week after its rating was cut to “sell” from
“hold” at  UOB-Kay Hian Holdings Ltd. (UOBK) , which cited the stock’s
“rich valuations.”  The stock dropped 5.9 percent to 4.60 ringgit at 4:42 p.m.
local time in Kuala Lumpur trading, set for its steepest decline
since Sept 26.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chan Tien Hin at 
 thchan@bloomberg.net  